CASE STUDY : ONLINE ORDERS MANAGEMENT SYSTEM

Aggregate Functions:

1. Find Minimum Order Amount

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $group:{
  _id:null,
  minAmount:{$min:"$totalAmount"}
 }
}
])



2. Find Maximum Order Amount

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $group:{
  _id:null,
  maxAmount:{$max:"$totalAmount"}
 }
}
])



3. Find Average Order Amount

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $group:{
  _id:null,
  avgAmount:{$avg:"$totalAmount"}
 }
}
])



4. Find Total Number of Orders

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $group:{
  _id:null,
  totalOrders:{$sum:1}
 }
}
])



5. Find Total Revenue

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $group:{
  _id:null,
  totalRevenue:{$sum:"$totalAmount"}
 }
}
])

Aggregation Pipeline Stages:

6. Filter Orders Greater Than 10000

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $match:{
  totalAmount:{$gt:10000}
 }
}
])



7. Show Only Customer Name and Amount

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $project:{
  customerName:1,
  totalAmount:1,
  _id:0
 }
}
])



8. Limit Results

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $limit:5
 }
])



9. Skip First 3 Orders

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $skip:3
 }
])



10. Sort by Total Amount Descending

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $sort:{
  totalAmount:-1
 }
}
])



11. Group by Category with Revenue Details

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $group:{
  _id:"$category",
  totalRevenue:{$sum:"$totalAmount"},
  avgAmount:{$avg:"$totalAmount"},
  maxAmount:{$max:"$totalAmount"},
  minAmount:{$min:"$totalAmount"},
  count:{$sum:1}
 }
}
])

Using $limit and $skip in MongoDB Aggregate:

12. Skip and Limit (Pagination)

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $skip:5
},
{
 $limit:5
}
])



13. Sorting with Pagination

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $sort:{
  totalAmount:-1
 }
},
{
 $skip:2
},
{
 $limit:3
}
])



14. Total Revenue by Category for Orders Above 10000

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $match:{
  totalAmount:{$gt:10000}
 }
},
{
 $group:{
  _id:"$category",
  totalRevenue:{$sum:"$totalAmount"}
 }
},
{
 $project:{
  category:"$_id",
  totalRevenue:1,
  _id:0
 }
},
{
 $sort:{
  totalRevenue:-1
 }
}
])



15. Top 3 Products with Highest Average Amount

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $group:{
  _id:"$product",
  avgAmount:{$avg:"$totalAmount"}
 }
},
{
 $project:{
  product:"$_id",
  avgAmount:1,
  _id:0
 }
},
{
 $sort:{
  avgAmount:-1
 }
},
{
 $limit:3
}
])



16. Display 3 Customers After Skipping First 2

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $project:{
  customerName:1,
  totalAmount:1,
  _id:0
 }
},
{
 $sort:{
  totalAmount:-1
 }
},
{
 $skip:2
},
{
 $limit:3
}
])



17. Count Orders Per Category where Quantity > 2

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $match:{
  quantity:{$gt:2}
 }
},
{
 $group:{
  _id:"$category",
  count:{$sum:1}
 }
},
{
 $match:{
  count:{$gt:1}
 }
},
{
 $sort:{
  count:1
 }
}
])



18. Total Quantity Sold Per Category

db.orders.aggregate([
{
 $group:{
  _id:"$category",
  totalQty:{$sum:"$quantity"}
 }
},
{
 $sort:{
  totalQty:-1
 }
},
{
 $skip:1
},
{
 $limit:2
}
